q: Would it be better for me if I just started a http server on localhost instead of using a custom protocol? Are custom protocols buggy?

Thanks for the test case!

> Are custom protocols buggy?

Nope, they work fine for their intended behavior.
Thanks a bundle for helping me resolve this one! Good work. :)
When should the `registerStandardSchemes` and `registerServiceWorkerSchemes` methods be used? I'm a bit confused about those two.

Well if you want the pages loaded over custom schemes to handle service workers then should register with `registerServiceWorkerSchemes`. `registerStandardSchemes` should be used for the scenarios described in the [documentation](https://github.com/electron/electron/blob/master/docs/api/protocol.md#protocolregisterstandardschemesschemes)
